  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Lives in Chad (SLIC)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Temporary employment in fodder generation; 2) Seeds and tools distribution; 3) Rent-to-own asset recovery; 4) Kitchen gardening; 5) Rotating Savings and Credit Associations (ROSCAs)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Internally displaced persons (IDPs), Returnees, Host populations</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project meets the immediate needs of the internally displaced person (IDP) population while helping them to become more self-sufficient. Cash for Work (CFW) activities which inject cash into the local economy are focused on fostering community between IDPs and host families and impact the degraded range land around the sites. Other program activities provide capital in the form of assets to entrepreneurs and a savings and loan strategy to provide access to cash for groups of women during this upcoming hunger season. WCDO will assist IDPs, returnees and host populations with rainy and dry season agriculture through the provision of improved seeds and animal traction devices which will positively impact their food security throughout the year. Finally, WCDO will provide training to the most vulnerable IDPs in year-round sack gardening.</narrative>
  </description>
